[t:0x0c0a,n:text]
{
    // Dry Planet
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Welcome to Rigel, human! It's been many years since our world has seen beings like you - some of us already believed the ancient hieroglyphs of the Empire of Stars to be a myth! Well met.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Rigel is the home star of us Droog. We have two planets: this is Geb, the other is Ixchel. Ixchel was settled millennia ago, long before the Empire of Stars, and due to the different climate there the Droog evolved a bit differently. Mudheads we call them, lovingly. While Geb is blessed with eternal sunshine, and bright stars at night, Ixchel is always shrouded in clouds that rain almost constantly. A rather unpleasant planet, if you ask me.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "According to our hieroglyph records, the Droog were one of the founding races of the Empire of Stars, but we always stayed a little apart and kept a certain autonomy. Maybe the other races got along a bit better because they were all humans in various shapes and sizes - from dwarves to giants.
When the Empire crumbled we were also the first ones to withdraw from the whole thing and let the humans fight their internecine wars among themselves.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "What are you saying, there are still Droog living in your world, Aranna? Amazing! Do bring them here!
One of our ancient sagas tell about a Droog colony in an Arannan province. To be honest it seems like it was a sort of prison - wrongdoers were expelled from Geb for a while, and of course they didn't want to serve their time on Ixchel. When we broke off from the Empire, it seems they were simply left to their own fate. The saga spends a hundred verses singing about how reckless that was and how much guilt the ancient rulers have laden upon all of us...";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "So you are looking for a sort of key for the ancient interstellar teleporter? We have none here. The smaller pad connects us to Ixchel, and it doesn't require any Starstone - when the system was built, the Droog insisted on this. We don't use it often - sometimes young Mudheads come looking around, be amazed by the stars at night, get a sunburn the next day, and return home, haha.
If you want to search for this ancient Starstone artifact, I can recommend you where to look: in the Pyramid. It's far out in the shrubs, however, and the shrubs are endless and wayless. The easiest way to find the Pyramid would be by finding the Golden Lion first. It's straight to the south from here - you can't miss it - go south, and then follow the eyes of the black cats. The eyes of the Lion will then point you directly to the Pyramid to the east.
Good luck! And beware of the Sand Imps, and especially of the savage Droog living out there! They will not like you strange creatures invading their territory. They'll most probably attack you. Buy some good weapons in our stores before you go.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Welcome, stranger. Here in my shop I sell the best bows you can find anywhere in the endless shrubland.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Good day, human. Would you like to purchase a shield from me? Or maybe a magic ring or amulet to protect you from the wild beasts and imps? Have a look at my shop!";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Greetings, dear alien, may the Goddess of the Sun always shine Her blessings upon you.
Would you be interested in a good sword or axe? Please have a look at my supplies.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Welcome to Rigel! Have you noticed Rigel is a blue star? The most beautiful color a sun can have.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Welcome to planet Geb of Rigel! Our planet is blessed with eternal sunshine. Unlike Ixchel, haha, always cloudy there.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Welcome to Oasis True Alpha! Rigel is the true Alpha Orionis, in case you didn't know.";
        to = "";
    }

    // Wet Planet
    // town center - town quest & tragg shops
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Hail, stranger, though I cannot say well met.  As you can see, our fair town has been besieged by Savages.  Many of us have been driven from our homes and businesses.  The populace is terrified, and I'm afraid we won't be able to help you much until the Savage-Folk are driven out.  Will you help to liberate our town?

The Savages are occupying houses to the south, east, and south-west from here.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "It must have been an aeon that humans have set foot on this world. Our scriptures prophesy star-folk coming down to save our ancient city. Might this be you? I suspect so, as there is no such thing as coincidence... I hope you will do as foretold, and help us, for we have been unable to help ourselves.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "You must aid us in our time of need... Have you driven out the Savages?";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "I and my people thank you, alien. This is no doubt a sign from the Angels that our redemption is close at hand. Your mission is quite troubling, though.  I know of no such Starstone item as you describe.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "You must seek the Skull of the Fallen God. It is out in the Wetlands. You cannot miss it, it is really huge. According to tradition, it is the fossil of a Creator God that fell from the sky. It is a place of miracles - you might find what you search for there. Be warned that the area is also overrun with Savage-Folk, though.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Seek out the Fallen One if you wish to find your way.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "I am happy for your good fortune and that the Fallen One was able to provide you a new way. Fortune smiles upon you stranger.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Ah!  Greetings, greetings, greetings!  I would be delighted to sell an animal to you...  however, with the Savages running about, I am wary.  Should your pack animal get killed, there are no refunds.  Come back once the threat of the Savages has been taken care of.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "These poor beasts are all I have. Are you in need of a good pack-animal, good sirs? Try the mare... she has a kick, but is loyal and true!";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "An alien! Then the light of the Angels shines on us again! Though with these Savage-Folk attacking, I would not feel safe letting you take one of my animals .. When the threat is over come talk to me again and I will gladly sell one of them to you.";
        to = "";
    }
    // mage island
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "You'd best find another route, my friend. The Savage-Folk are vicious. They've taken the buildings over the bridge here - I've got my hands full just keeping them at bay.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "You went through those Savages like a Butchering Scimitar of Refreshment goes through sun-soft mungo butter... Good work!";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "If you drive out the Savages, I will feel free to unlock my wares for sale, and I will tell you of a dream I had...";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "In my dreams I saw you, alien. A great storm heralded your arrival and the wind spoke of your name to me. An ill wind it was, full of dread and destruction. But when the storm had passed, the land was washed clean and my people were finally redeemed. Please, peruse my wares. I am sure you will not be disappointed.";
        to = "";
    }
    // potions island
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Hail, stranger. I am amazed to see anyone visiting our town, what with all the Savages out there - let alone humans, which we only knew from ancient scripture.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Xaman'Ek has potions that do more than heal, stranger. Some can harm as well. Be careful what you buy from her.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Not much to offer to slake your thirst, stranger... care to try a little Phrak Juice Cocktail?";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Best be on your guard, my friend. The Savages have overrun much of the town. I'm sorry I don't have much to offer you in the way of drink... care to try a little Phrak Juice Cocktail?";
        to = "";
    }
    // smithy island
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "I am not surprised to see that aliens have finally arrived here. Tis a sure sign of the dawn of a new age. It's the final countdown, of that there is no doubt...";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Once those Savages are wiped out, I'll break out my goods for sale.";
        to = "";
    }
    // house islands
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "I greet you with honor and would speak with you plainly, alien. My name is Uyitzin, an artist and singer of songs. The Savages have gone too far, and killed my beloved Xpiayoc.  Avenge her for me.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Greetings, stranger! I cannot speak with the city under attack by the Savages. Once you've cleared the city of the beasts, I have a favor to ask. Come back then; I do not wish to burden you with it now.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "I would ask a favor of you... My brother, Necahual, works at the potion shop out in the Wetlands, between the Human Ruins and the Skull of the Fallen God.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "It was his shift when the Savages attacked, and he has not returned... Please - find my brother, and make sure he is safe.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Thank you-I'm so happy that Necahual is safe!";
        to = "";
    }
    // Wetlands
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Please, I beg of you, the Altar must be purified. The Fleshrender grows stronger with every day.";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Take this icon. I have stolen it from the Human Shrine ahead. It must have kept that monster banished. Now it is too late for me to repent... I'm dying. Please, you must...";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "The Fallen One be praised! You have slain the Fleshrender that afflicted the Altar. Please, take this holy icon and place it back upon the Altar, that the foul taint of my careless theft will be cleansed. Then, my sacrilege will be amended...";
        to = "";
    }
    [0x0000]
    {
        from = "Wow - you're a real human! I've been studying the ancient scriptures a lot... Well, pleased to meet you. Thanks for rescuing me and all. My name is Necahual, I work at the potion shop ahead. I was alone when the Savages came - I had to run, and was able to barricade myself in here. If you can free it, help yourself to any potions you find there!
And greet my sister Ah-Cun-Can in Orionis, she's probably worried about me. Tell her I'm fine. I'm not hurt and there are provisions in this shack.";
        to = "";
    }
}
